argument.description: An expression that specifies a row that is hypothetically inserted into a group of rows.
An expression that specifies a row that is hypothetically inserted into a group of rows.
Specifies the order of the rows from the same grouping set that are processed in the aggregation.

description: The CUME_DIST function returns the cumulative distribution of a row that is hypothetically inserted into a group of rows.
sample:
SELECT CUME_DIST(47000) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY SALARY) 
      INTO :CD FROM EMPLOYEE WHERE WORKDEPT = 'A00'
